astraiea.layer2

Class Layer2

  • java.lang.Object
    • astraiea.layer2.Layer2

  • public final class Layer2
extends java.lang.Object
    Layer2 organises the running of two or more metaheuristics. It then passes the results onto Layer1 for analysing.
    Author:
    Geoffrey Neumann, Jerry Swan

      • runArtefacts

        public static <T extends GeneratorOutput> java.util.List<Result> runArtefacts(SetOfComparisons<MultipleArtefactOutput<T>> gens,
                                                                              double significanceThreshold,
                                                                              IncrementingStrategy incr,
                                                                              java.util.Random random,
                                                                              boolean censoring)
        Running with or without censoring with datapoint or timeseries generators with multiple artefacts. This means that options such as Brunnermunzel which would otherwise (and in the case of datapoint) be optional with no censoring are now never allowed anyway. The same method call is therefore used for both datapoint and timeseries censoring and no censoring- no difference in options. See runAllImpl for an explanation of the parameters.
        Parameters:
        gens - set of generators being compared
        significanceThreshold - value above which a p value is considered significant
        incr - how runs should be repeated, whether only for a fixed amount of runs or whether it should increment
        artefactRepeats - if using multiple artefacts then each run constitutes a single artefact and this specifies how many repeats should be done with that artefact
        random - random number generator for running the generators
        Returns:
        object holding p value, effect size etc. for every comparison for which results are required
